in the dramatic arts, karen Zimmerman
teaches a program of creative cosmetics for
children ranging from 1st to 4th grades. Analagous to the free use of diﬂevent media in the
visual arts, Miss Zimmerman's goal is [0 make
the children at ease and help them discover
their natural creativity, while adding subtle hints
about features and techniques. Miss Zimmerman
worked last session with 14 children of wider age
range with a more conventional approach and
concluded the lessons with a production. Credo
time (lramatlcs, however, does not include production. ‘
The emphasis means toward more formal training in basic dramatic techniques in junior high
classes, according to Max Helfgotll Heligott, assisted by Dennis Rich, works with 20 Children
and anticipated a production at the end of the
session. Last year the junior high group, taught
by Howard earned, wrote and produced an original melodrama.
The Art automation is planning to sponsor a
spring art sale, possibly open air. in late May.
cornell students, along with artists from Marshalllown, Newton, and Oskaloosa, will be invited
to show their work, according to Mrs. purple.
The Park Street house, acquired by the association February 15, is being center from the
college. Publicity for the children’s art classes
through [he public schools has been requested.
